<chapter xml:id="ch-personal-finance" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Personal Finance</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>In this chapter, we will cover simple and compound interest, credit cards, loans, and annuities. The goal is to provide insight into how these financial concepts work. </p>
    <note>
	<p>
		All information provided in this chapter is for educational purposes only and should not be used as the sole basis for making financial decisions or as a replacement for a qualified financial advisor. The formulas and examples provided here cover a limited range of scenarios and some are based on simplified assumptions. 
	</p>
 </note>
  </introduction>

